text: Pervomayskoye () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Pervomaysky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 918 as of 2010. There are 10 streets. == Geography == It is located 67 km from Sterlitamak. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlitamaksky District
title: Pervomayskoye, Sterlitamaksky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
